<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using elimination.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}-{6}{y}={110}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{8}{x}-{7}{y}=-{1}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{8},-{9}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to use the first equation to eliminate x from the second equation.</p>
<p>To eliminate we need the scaled version of equation one to have a coefficient of -8. So we scale by <m>\displaystyle-\frac{{8}}{{-{{7}}}}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{{8}}}{{-{{7}}}}{\left(-{7}{x}+-{6}{y}\right)}=-\frac{{{8}}}{{-{{7}}}}{\left({110}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{\left({8}\right)}{x}+-{6.8571428571429}{y}={125.71428571429}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{8}{x}-{7}{y}=-{1}</m></p>
<p>Adding these two equations gives us</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{13.857142857143}{y}={124.71428571429}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{124.71428571429}}{{-{{13.857142857143}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{9}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}+-{6}{\left(-{9}\right)}={110}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}+{\left({54}\right)}={110}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}={110}-{\left({54}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{7}{x}={56}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{56}}{{-{{7}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{8}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{8},-{9}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

